            <title>[LU-7471] In Lustre sanity HSM tests make_large_for_*() functions shadow free space failure</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-7471</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;1. Prepare Lustre with less than 100MB of free space.&lt;br/&gt;
2. Run test 200 of HSM sanity check in prepared Lustre.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Issue reproduced if test fails (typically due to errors in awk script called later in the test function).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Issue fixed if test ends with &apos;SKIP&apos; outcome and message &quot;not enough free space&quot;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
